			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Tanana, I think the spell you are refering to is Gate (lvl 5 spell).  Gate teleports you from ANYWHERE in Norrath to the point where you go when you die (nice for getting out of trouble).  Whereas Bind Affinity SETS the point where you go when you either DIE or GATE to your current location. So for me ,an Iksar , if I plan on spending time at the Lake of Ill Omen, I would BIND myself to that area so that if I DIE or GATE, I won't end up in the Field of Bones, I'll just go back to a safe point in the Lake area.  Hope this helps.<BR>
<BR>
lvl 8 Iksar Shaman - Brell Serilis
				</font>
			</td>

